          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Ensuring Access to Quality Recovery Living Act of 2018</strong></p> <p>This bill requires the Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration (SAMHSA)&nbsp;to publish best practices for operating recovery housing, to distribute such publication to the states, and to provide technical assistance to states seeking to adopt such practices. &nbsp;SAMHSA must require states to follow such best practices in order to receive a contract or grant for recovery housing.&nbsp;"Recovery housing" means a shared living environment free from alcohol and illegal drug use and centered on peer support and connection to services to promote recovery from substance use disorders.</p>]]></text>
